
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
	<style>
* {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

input[type=text], select, textarea {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 12px;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  border-radius: 4px;
  resize: vertical;
}

input[type=submit] {
  background-color: #4CAF50;
  color: white;
  padding: 12px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
  float: right;
}

/* Responsive layout - when the screen is less than 600px wide, make the two columns stack on top of each other instead of next to each other */
@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  .col-25, .col-75, input[type=submit] {
    width: 100%;
    margin-top: 0;
  }
}
</style>
  
  </head>
    <body>
<form action="/reviewed" method="post">
<h2>Rate each of these categories on a scale of 1-5, 1 being completely inaccessible for you and 5 being as accessible as possible.</h2>
  Username: <input type="text" name="username"><br>
 Business: <input type="text" name="business"><br>

<h3>Entrance</h3>
<h4>For example: 
<ul>
<li>Was there a ramp entrance at the front?
<li>Or, were there labeled directions to the ramp entrance?
</ul></h4>
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="1"> 1
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="2"> 2
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="3"> 3
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="4"> 4
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="5"> 5<br>


<div>
<textarea name="comments1" id="comments1" style="font-family:sans-serif;font-size:1.2em;">
Comments?
</textarea>
</div>

<h3>Navigation</h3>
<h4>For example: 
<ul>
<li>Was there a lowered counter for wheelchair access? Was it clutter free? 
<li>Was there a place for wheelchair seating? 
<li>Are the steps brightly marked?</ul></h4>
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="1"> 1
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="2"> 2
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="3"> 3
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="4"> 4
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="5"> 5<br>


<div>
<textarea name="comments2" id="comments2" style="font-family:sans-serif;font-size:1.2em;">
Comments?
</textarea>
</div>

<h3>Bathrooms</h3>
<h4>For example: 
<ul>
<li>Was there a braille label? 
<li>Was the accessible bathroom in the front or the back? 
<li>Was there an accessible bathroom at all?</h4>
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="1"> 1
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="2"> 2
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="3"> 3
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="4"> 4
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="5"> 5<br>


<div>
<textarea name="comments3" id="comments3" style="font-family:sans-serif;font-size:1.2em;">
Comments?
</textarea>
</div>

<h3>Product/Service</h3>
<h4>For example: 
<ul>
<li>Did they have a braille menu? 
<li>Did they have a pool lift?</ul></h4>
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="1"> 1
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="2"> 2
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="3"> 3
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="4"> 4
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="5"> 5<br>


<div>
<textarea name="comments4" id="comments4" style="font-family:sans-serif;font-size:1.2em;">
Comments?
</textarea>
</div>

<h3>Employee Interaction</h3>
<h4>For example: 
<ul>
<li>Did they use person first language? 
<li>Did they read the menu for you when asked? 
<li>Did they allow service animals?</ul></h4>
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="1"> 1
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="2"> 2
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="3"> 3
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="4"> 4
<input type="radio" name="rating" value="5"> 5<br>


